Recommended for to control sucking pest Spray any one of the following insecticides in the initial stage of infestation 
Spray dimethoate 30 EC 500 ml/ha 
Spray Methyl demeton (metasystox 25 ec) 25 EC@ 500 ml/ha.
Spray imedachlorprid 17.8 SL (Admire, confidor 200 SC, 250 ml per hectare) 5-7 ml at 15 liter of water.
 Spray fipronil (Regent)@ 25 ml at 15 liter of water.
Spray Lambda Cyhalothrin 5% EC 120 to 150 ml at per acre or 12-15 ml per pump.
Triazofos 40 EC 20-25 ml per pump 
profenophos 40 % 20-25 ml per pump
Azadirachtin 0.03% Min. Neem Oil Based E.C. Containing 40-45 ml per pump
Fenthion 100 EC 1 ml per liter or 15-17 ml per pump 
Spray Carbaryl (4 g/litre of water) or Metacid (1ml/litre of water) during the seedling stage effectively controls the pest.
 Spray Buprofezin 25% SC ( Jawaa, Apple and Bruno  ) @ 320 ml /acre Spray Spray Etofenprox  10%EC ( Bambard or Nukil) @ 400 ML / acre   
Spray Thiacloprid 21.7 % SC @ 6.0 ml/10 lit. 
Spray Oxydemeton –Methyl 25 % EC @ 1.0 ml/lit. 
Spray Dichlorvos 76% EC @ 250-350 ml/acre. 
Spray daiphenthuran 50 % WP (pegasas) 10 to 15 gram at per pump.
Spray of Acephate 75% SP @ 300-400 gm/acre
Use recommended dose of monocrotophos 36 % 1500 ML or imidachlorprid 125 ML or ethipol+imidachlorprid 150 ML per hectare.

KCCAns:
Trichoderma

Trichoderma is a biological fungicide that regulates soil and seed borne diseases in plants.
Seed treatment is used at the rate of 5-6 grams per kg of seeds. Use 1 kg of trichoderma in soil treatment by mixing 100 kg of good cooked manure and using it during the last boiler time.
Cutting and Root Treatment- Mix 200 grams of Trichoderma in 15-20 liters of water and treat the roots and cuttings of planting plants for 10 minutes in this solution.
Violet disease is controlled by making 3 grams of Trichoderma per liter of water and spraying 3-4 times on a standing crop at 10-15 days intervals.

1- Visit the field in which sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with hand and make a round pile by putting it on clean clothes. Remove the clay from finger to four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure until almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. Insert a notice sheet with a sample on which all the information is written, inside a plastic bag and outside a garment bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.
